lessons.theory:
# Reading one task: route parameters

> **Goal:** add a dynamic route to fetch a single task by its id.

## Learn

To read **one** task you need its id in the URL: `GET /tasks/1`, `GET /tasks/2`… You don't write a route per id — you use a **parameter**, in curly braces:

```js
ROUTE('GET /tasks/{id}', function($) {
    var id = $.params.id;   // '1', '2', ...
    $.json({ id: id });
});
```

`$.params.id` gives you whatever was in that slot. Params arrive as **text**, so compare loosely (`==`) or convert with `+id`.

## Build it in Tasker

Find the task whose id matches and return it. If there isn't one, reply with `$.invalid`:

```js
ROUTE('GET /tasks/{id}', function($) {
    var task = tasks.find(function(t) { return t.id == $.params.id; });
    if (!task) {
        $.invalid('Task not found');
        return;
    }
    $.json(task);
});
```

