lessons.theory:
# Creating a task: reading the body

> **Goal:** accept a new task sent by the client and add it.

## Learn

To **create** something, the client sends data in the request **body** as JSON. You read it with `$.body`:

```js
ROUTE('POST /tasks', function($) {
    var title = $.body.title;
    var task = { id: Date.now(), title: title, done: false };
    tasks.push(task);
    $.success(task);
});
```

- `$.body` is the parsed JSON the client sent.
- `$.success(value)` replies `{ success: true, value }` — the convention for "it worked".

## Build it in Tasker

Add `POST /tasks` that reads `$.body.title`, creates a task and returns it. We'll send it `{ "title": "Read a book" }`.

