lessons.theory:
# Actions & validation

> **Goal:** run a schema action from a route and let the schema guard the gate.

## Learn

A schema isn't just a description — it hosts **actions**, the operations you can run on that data. You add one with `schema.action`:

```js
schema.action('insert', {
    action: function($, model) {
        // `model` is the validated input — title is guaranteed to be present
        $.success({ id: 1, title: model.title, done: false });
    }
});
```

To run it from a route, call **`$.action`** with the request body:

```js
ROUTE('POST /tasks', function($) {
    $.action('Task/insert', $.body);
});
```

Here's the payoff: before your `action` runs, Total.js **validates** `$.body` against the schema. Send `{ "title": "Buy milk" }` and it works. Send `{ }` and the request is **rejected** automatically with a "Required: title" error — your code never even runs.

## Build it in Tasker

Wire `POST /tasks` to the `Task/insert` action. The schema (already defined above) does the validating for you.

