# Tasks from the database

> **Goal:** swap Tasker's in-memory array for the database.

## Learn

Remember Tasker's array of tasks? Let's store them in the database instead. The routes barely change — they just talk to `DB()`:

```js
var db = DB();

exports.install = function() {

    // List
    ROUTE('GET /tasks', function($) {
        db.find('tasks').callback(function(err, rows) {
            $.json(rows);
        });
    });

    // Create
    ROUTE('POST /tasks', function($) {
        db.insert('tasks', { title: $.body.title, done: false });
        $.success();
    });
};
```

Now tasks are real records — they don't disappear when the app restarts.

