lessons.theory:
# Read one & update

> **Goal:** finish wiring Tasker's API to the database.

## Learn

To work with **one** record, filter by id with `.where`:

```js
// Read one
db.read('tasks').where('id', 1).callback(function(err, task) {
    console.log(task);
});

// Update matching rows
db.update('tasks', { done: true }).where('id', 1).callback(function(err) {
    console.log('Updated!');
});

// Delete matching rows
db.remove('tasks').where('id', 1).callback();
```

- **`read`** returns a single record (the first match).
- **`update(table, changes)`** applies the changes to matching rows.
- **`remove(table)`** deletes matching rows.

> Route params are **text**, so convert the id to a number with `+$.params.id` before comparing.

## Build it in Tasker

Make `PUT /tasks/{id}` mark a task **done** in the database, then return it.

