DEF.onAudit = function(name, log) {
    console.log('Stored audit:', log.message, '— by', log.username);
};

var $ = { user: { name: 'Ada' } };
AUDIT($, 'Task created');

lessons.theory:
# Background jobs & the rest of the toolbox

> **Goal:** know what else lives in Total.js's toolbox.

## Background jobs

Some work shouldn't block a request — sending a weekly digest, cleaning up old tasks. Total.js runs **services** on a schedule:

```js
ON('service', function(counter) {
    // counter increases every minute
    if (counter % 60 === 0) {
        // once an hour — e.g. remove tasks done long ago
    }
});
```

## More tools you'll reach for

Total.js bundles a deep standard library, so you rarely need third-party packages:

- **`RESTBuilder`** — call other HTTP APIs.
- **`Mail`** — send emails (e.g. "your task is due").
- **`Images`** — resize and convert images.
- **`FileStorage`** — store uploads and generated files.

Reach for these instead of reinventing them.

## Build it in Tasker

Tasker now has settings, utilities and graceful errors — a robust backend. There's just one thing missing: a **face**. Next module we give Tasker a web page and live updates. 🎨

