# Load & save with TAPI

> **Goal:** load and create tasks through the backend's API routes.

## Learn

`TAPI(name, data, callback)` calls a named **API operation** at `/api/` — the exact operations you declared in the backend:

```js
// Load the list into the model (the repeater re-renders automatically):
TAPI('tasks_list', function(response) {
    SET('tasks', response);
});

// Create a task, then refresh:
TAPI('tasks_insert', { title: 'Buy milk' }, function(response) {
    TAPI('tasks_list', function(r) { SET('tasks', r); });
});
```

The client never hardcodes URLs — it names the operation, and Total.js routes it to the schema action on the server. Validation, errors and auth all happen on the backend exactly as you built them.

> 🔁 This is the round trip: the **same `tasks_list` operation** from `ROUTE('API /api/ -tasks_list *Tasks --> list')` is what `TAPI('tasks_list')` calls. One name, both sides.

# Real-time with WAPI

> **Goal:** keep every open Tasker in sync, live.

## Learn

Open a socket with the **j-WebSocket** component, then use **`WAPI()`** just like `TAPI()` — but messages flow both ways, instantly:

```html
<ui-component name="websocket" config="url:/live/;reconnect:3000"></ui-component>
```

```js
// Same call style, over the socket:
WAPI('tasks_list', function(response) {
    SET('tasks', response);
});

// And react to pushes from the server (e.g. someone assigned you a task):
ON('@task_assigned', function(task) {
    // show a notification, refresh the list…
});
```

Pair this with the backend's `SOCKET` route and the assign/notify flow from *Sharing & notifications*: when a task is shared with you, the server pushes it and your list updates with no refresh.

## Built-in feedback
Combine with **`j-Message`**, **`j-Confirm`** and **`j-Loading`** for notifications, confirmations and spinners — all components, no extra libraries.

# React to changes with WATCH

> **Goal:** run code automatically whenever a value changes.

## Learn

**`WATCH(path, fn)`** calls your function every time the model at `path` changes — perfect for derived state, autosave, or logging:

```js
WATCH('task.title', function(value) {
    SET('status', value ? ('Editing: ' + value) : 'Empty');
});
```

Now `status` updates itself whenever `task.title` changes — you never call it by hand. (Use `WATCH('*', fn)` to watch everything.)

## Build it in Tasker

`WATCH` the path `task.title`; when it changes, `SET('status', 'changed: ' + value)`. The **Rename** button sets the title — clicking it should update the status via your watcher.

# Waiting for data (WAIT)

> **Goal:** run code the moment some data exists — even if it arrives later.

## Learn

Often data isn't there yet (it's loading from the server). **`WAIT(path, fn)`** runs your function as soon as `path` has a value — now, or whenever it shows up:

```js
WAIT('tasks', function() {
    SET('status', 'Loaded ' + GET('tasks').length + ' tasks');
});
```

If `tasks` is already set, it runs immediately. If not, jComponent remembers and fires the moment something does `SET('tasks', ...)` — perfect after a `TAPI` load. No polling, no callbacks to thread through.

## Build it in Tasker

`tasks` starts empty. Register a `WAIT('tasks', ...)` that sets `status` to a "Loaded N tasks" message. The **Load** button does `SET('tasks', [...])` — clicking it should make your WAIT fire.

